Detailed Description

M2m runtime status for the m2m processing request. Used to get time at different processing step/point.

sturct Vps_M2mIntfFrameStats

Field Documentation

UInt32 Vps_M2mIntfFrameStats::dequeueTimeStamp

time at which the request is returned from the driver, essentially, when getProcessRequest is called

UInt32 Vps_M2mIntfFrameStats::endProcTimeStamp

time at which processing for the request is completed and request complete ISR is called. This time is taken in the request complete ISR handler

UInt32 Vps_M2mIntfFrameStats::queueTimeStamp

time at which the request is submitted to the driver

UInt32 Vps_M2mIntfFrameStats::startProcTimeStamp

time at which processing for the request is started, Typically when DMA engine or input/output modules is started for the processing
